              <!-- %h3.entry-title{:rel => 'bookmark'}= link_to_page(@page) -->
              <h3 class='entry-title'><a href="/draft/better-tests">Better Tests</a></h3>
              <div class='entry-content'>
                <ul>
                <li>Yehuda's talk at RubyConf</li>
                <li>more emphasis on acceptance tests/public API tests</li>
                <li>since those give better confidence and more "business value"</li>
                <li>unit tests still good and important</li>
                <li>difference is unit tests useful for developers, whereas acceptance tests are useful for developers (refactoring) <em>and</em> users (other developers, end users)</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
